  <Name>k__BackingField: 2 Thessalonians
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 2th
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: '    Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy,To the church of the Thessalonians
        in God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Thanksgiving'
      title: Thanksgiving
      number: 2
      content: 'Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  We ought always to give thanks to God for you, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        as is right, because your faith is growing abundantly, and the love of every
        one of you for one another is increasing. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: "Or . In New Testament usage, depending on the context, the plural
          Greek word (translated \u201Cbrothers\u201D) may refer either to or to "
    - name: "4: The Judgment at Christ\u2019s Coming"
      title: "The Judgment at Christ\u2019s Coming"
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore we ourselves boast about you in the churches of God for
        your steadfastness and faith in all your persecutions and in the afflictions
        that you are enduring.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "This is evidence of the righteous judgment of God, that you may be
        considered worthy of the kingdom of God, for which you are also suffering\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'since indeed God considers it just to repay with affliction those
        who afflict you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and to grant relief to you who are afflicted as well as to us, when
        the Lord Jesus is revealed from heaven with his mighty angels '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'in flaming fire, inflicting vengeance on those who do not know God
        and on those who do not obey the gospel of our Lord Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They will suffer the punishment of eternal destruction, away from[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the presence of the Lord and from the glory of his might, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'when he comes on that day to be glorified in his saints, and to be
        marveled at among all who have believed, because our testimony to you was
        believed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'To this end we always pray for you, that our God may make you worthy
        of his calling and may fulfill every resolve for good and every work of faith
        by his power, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: so that the name of our Lord Jesus may be glorified in you, and you
        in him, according to the grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Man of Lawlessness'
      title: The Man of Lawlessness
      number: 1
      content: '  Now concerning the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ and our being
        gathered together to him, we ask you, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Or ; also verses 13, 15
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'not to be quickly shaken in mind or alarmed, either by a spirit or
        a spoken word, or a letter seeming to be from us, to the effect that the
        day of the Lord has come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let no one deceive you in any way. For that day will not come, unless
        the rebellion comes first, and the man of lawlessness[[COMMENT(0)]] is revealed,
        the son of destruction,  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: Some manuscripts Greek (a Hebrew idiom)
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'who opposes and exalts himself against every so-called god or object
        of worship, so that he takes his seat in the temple of God, proclaiming himself
        to be God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do you not remember that when I was still with you I told you these
        things? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And you know what is restraining him now so that he may be revealed
        in his time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the mystery of lawlessness is already at work. Only he who now
        restrains it will do so until he is out of the way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And then the lawless one will be revealed, whom the Lord Jesus will
        kill with the breath of his mouth and bring to nothing by the appearance
        of his coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The coming of the lawless one is by the activity of Satan with all
        power and false signs and wonders, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and with all wicked deception for those who are perishing, because
        they refused to love the truth and so be saved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore God sends them a strong delusion, so that they may believe
        what is false, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Stand Firm'
      title: Stand Firm
      number: 12
      content: 'in order that all may be condemned who did not believe the truth
        but had pleasure in unrighteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But we ought always to give thanks to God for you, brothers beloved
        by the Lord, because God chose you as the firstfruits[[COMMENT(0)]]  to be
        saved, through sanctification by the Spirit and belief in the truth. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:13 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'To this he called you through our gospel, so that you may obtain
        the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So then, brothers, stand firm and hold to the traditions that you
        were taught by us, either by our spoken word or by our letter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now may our Lord Jesus Christ himself, and God our Father, who loved
        us and gave us eternal comfort and good hope through grace, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: comfort your hearts and establish them in every good work and word.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pray for Us'
      title: Pray for Us
      number: 1
      content: '  Finally, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]]  pray for us, that the word of
        the Lord may speed ahead and be honored, as happened among you, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: 'Or ; also verses 6, 13Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and that we may be delivered from wicked and evil men. For not all
        have faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But the Lord is faithful. He will establish you and guard you against
        the evil one.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And we have confidence in the Lord about you, that you are doing
        and will do the things that we command. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Warning Against Idleness'
      title: Warning Against Idleness
      number: 5
      content: 'May the Lord direct your hearts to the love of God and to the steadfastness
        of Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now we command you, brothers, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ,
        that you keep away from any brother who is walking in idleness and not in
        accord with the tradition that you received from us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For you yourselves know how you ought to imitate us, because we were
        not idle when we were with you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "nor did we eat anyone\u2019s bread without paying for it, but with
        toil and labor we worked night and day, that we might not be a burden to
        any of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It was not because we do not have that right, but to give you in
        ourselves an example to imitate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For even when we were with you, we would give you this command: If
        anyone is not willing to work, let him not eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For we hear that some among you walk in idleness, not busy at work,
        but busybodies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now such persons we command and encourage in the Lord Jesus Christ
        to do their work quietly and to earn their own living.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As for you, brothers, do not grow weary in doing good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If anyone does not obey what we say in this letter, take note of
        that person, and have nothing to do with him, that he may be ashamed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Benediction'
      title: Benediction
      number: 15
      content: 'Do not regard him as an enemy, but warn him as a brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now may the Lord of peace himself give you peace at all times in
        every way. The Lord be with you all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I, Paul, write this greeting with my own hand. This is the sign of
        genuineness in every letter of mine; it is the way I write. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all.
      comments: []
